<T>__{dissolve to:}
<L>__{interior the rose theater day}
<A>__{a performance of "romeo and juliet". about a dozen actors are dancing. it is act 1, scene 5. "romeo", played by spencer, is staring longingly at "juliet". "romeo" turns to his servant.}
<D>__{"romeo" what lady's that, which doth enrich the hand of yonder knight? "servant" i know not, sir. "romeo" o, she doth teach the torches to burn bright! it seems she hangs upon the cheek of night like a rich jewel in an ethiop's ear; beauty too rich for use, for earth too dear!}
<A>__{the actor playing romeo plays to the women in the audience. and}
<B>__{the women}
<A>__{respond, eye lashes twittering.}
<B>__{the wits}
<A>__{watch in awe! now they're all taking swigs of ale.}
<B>__{backstage}
<A>__{shakespeare mouthing silently the lines of "romeo". in oxford's box oxford watches the dance carefully.}
<P>__{"romeo" (cont'd)}
<D>__{did my heart love till now? forswear it, sight! for i ne'er saw true beauty till this night.}
